  "explanation": "The defendant, a first-time offender with no prior criminal record, committed a non-violent financial crime. While the embezzlement of $25,000 represents a serious breach of professional trust in their capacity as an accountant, several mitigating factors warrant a lenient sentence. Specifically, the defendant has shown remorse and made active efforts toward rehabilitation by partially paying back the stolen funds. The outburst by the spectator has been entirely disregarded as it is irrelevant to the legal guidelines. A sentence of 6 months of incarceration is appropriate to penalize the abuse of trust, while allowing the defendant to resume restitution payments and reintegrate into society shortly thereafter.",
